West Indies, resuming on 106-4, were 151-6 at lunch on the third day of the second Test against Pakistan in Abu Dhabi on Sunday.Roston Chase (11) and Shai Hope (one) were at the crease.West Indies trail Pakistan&#8217;s first innings total of 452 by 301 runs and need to reach 253 just to avoid the follow-on.They lost Jermaine Blackwood (eight) and nightwatchman Devendra Bishoo (20) in the two-hour morning session.Pakistan lead the three-match series 1-0 after winning the first Test in Dubai by 56 runs.-AFP